[32m+[m[32m<h2 id="help-navigation">Navigation</h2>[m
[32m+[m[32mStarting from the <a href="index.html">Overview</a> page, you can browse the documentation using the links in each page, and in the navigation bar at the top of each page. The <a href="index-files/index-1.html">Index</a> and Search box allow you to navigate to specific declarations and summary pages, including: <a href="allpackages-index.html">All Packages</a>, <a href="allclasses-index.html">All Classes and Interfaces</a>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="search">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>Search</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>You can search for definitions of modules, packages, types, fields, methods, system properties and other terms defined in the API. These items can be searched using part or all of the name, optionally using "camelCase" abbreviations, or multiple search terms separated by whitespace. Some examples:</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m<ul class="help-section-list">[m
[32m+[m[32m<li><code>"j.l.obj"</code> matches "java.lang.Object"</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li><code>"InpStr"</code> matches "java.io.InputStream"</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li><code>"math exact long"</code> matches "java.lang.Math.absExact(long)"</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m</ul>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>Refer to the <a href="https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/21/docs/specs/javadoc/javadoc-search-spec.html">Javadoc Search Specification</a> for a full description of search features.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
