[32m+[m[32m<div class="sub-title">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h2 id="help-pages">Kinds of Pages</h2>[m
[32m+[m[32mThe following sections describe the different kinds of pages in this collection.[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="package">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>Package</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>Each package has a page that contains a list of its classes and interfaces, with a summary for each. These pages may contain the following categories:</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m<ul class="help-section-list">[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Interfaces</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Classes</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Enum Classes</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Exception Classes</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Annotation Interfaces</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m</ul>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="class">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>Class or Interface</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>Each class, interface, nested class and nested interface has its own separate page. Each of these pages has three sections consisting of a declaration and description, member summary tables, and detailed member descriptions. Entries in each of these sections are omitted if they are empty or not applicable.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m<ul class="help-section-list">[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Class Inheritance Diagram</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Direct Subclasses</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>All Known Subinterfaces</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>All Known Implementing Classes</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Class or Interface Declaration</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Class or Interface Description</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m</ul>[m
[32m+[m[32m<br>[m
[32m+[m[32m<ul class="help-section-list">[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Nested Class Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Enum Constant Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Field Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Property Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Constructor Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Method Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Required Element Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Optional Element Summary</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m</ul>[m
[32m+[m[32m<br>[m
[32m+[m[32m<ul class="help-section-list">[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Enum Constant Details</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Field Details</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Property Details</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Constructor Details</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Method Details</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>Element Details</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m</ul>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p><span class="help-note">Note:</span> Annotation interfaces have required and optional elements, but not methods. Only enum classes have enum constants. The components of a record class are displayed as part of the declaration of the record class. Properties are a feature of JavaFX.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>The summary entries are alphabetical, while the detailed descriptions are in the order they appear in the source code. This preserves the logical groupings established by the programmer.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="doc-file">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>Other Files</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>Packages and modules may contain pages with additional information related to the declarations nearby.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="use">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>Use</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>Each documented package, class and interface has its own Use page.  This page describes what packages, classes, methods, constructors and fields use any part of the given class or package. Given a class or interface A, its Use page includes subclasses of A, fields declared as A, methods that return A, and methods and constructors with parameters of type A.  You can access this page by first going to the package, class or interface, then clicking on the USE link in the navigation bar.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="tree">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>Tree (Class Hierarchy)</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>There is a <a href="overview-tree.html">Class Hierarchy</a> page for all packages, plus a hierarchy for each package. Each hierarchy page contains a list of classes and a list of interfaces. Classes are organized by inheritance structure starting with <code>java.lang.Object</code>. Interfaces do not inherit from <code>java.lang.Object</code>.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m<ul class="help-section-list">[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>When viewing the Overview page, clicking on TREE displays the hierarchy for all packages.</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m<li>When viewing a particular package, class or interface page, clicking on TREE displays the hierarchy for only that package.</li>[m
[32m+[m[32m</ul>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="all-packages">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>All Packages</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>The <a href="allpackages-index.html">All Packages</a> page contains an alphabetic index of all packages contained in the documentation.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="all-classes">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>All Classes and Interfaces</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>The <a href="allclasses-index.html">All Classes and Interfaces</a> page contains an alphabetic index of all classes and interfaces contained in the documentation, including annotation interfaces, enum classes, and record classes.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
[32m+[m[32m<section class="help-section" id="index">[m
[32m+[m[32m<h3>Index</h3>[m
[32m+[m[32m<p>The <a href="index-files/index-1.html">Index</a> contains an alphabetic index of all classes, interfaces, constructors, methods, and fields in the documentation, as well as summary pages such as <a href="allpackages-index.html">All Packages</a>, <a href="allclasses-index.html">All Classes and Interfaces</a>.</p>[m
[32m+[m[32m</section>[m
